ANTHRAX, HUMAN - INDIA (KORAPUT): RFI
*************************************
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2003 16:29:55 +0100
From: A-Lan Banks <a-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: PTI (India)
<http://www.ptinews.com/createframes1.asp?main=&val=3>


Three people were killed and over 20 others affected by a disease termed by
local officials as "anthrax" in Lamtaput block of Koraput district over
thelast 15 days. No institute of repute has, so far, confirmed outbreak of
anthrax in the area. The deaths occurred in a private hospital at Lamtaput
where the victims had been admitted for treatment.

The sources said that the block development officer, had reported that a 29
year old from Patraput village, a 32 year old from Terraguda village and a
35 year old from Mahadeiput village died after they had been admitted to
hospital. The health authorities had rushed medical teams to the area to
contain the spread of the disease.

The outbreak had been reported from Dhadi, K.Maliput, Charaguda, Kangrapad,
Solipada, Mahadeiput, Chopadi and Andipoda villages, the sources said.
